- The Americas region reported 40.5% of cases and 36.4% of deaths in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 108.80 million cases. The USA reported 692 531 cases followed by Argentina, Canada, Brazil, Mexico, Columbia and Bolivia. An additional 16 countries reported more than 1000 cases (Peru, Chile, Cuba, Guatemala, Costa Rica, Panama, Dominican Republic, Uruguay, Jamaica, Puerto Rico, Panama, Barbados, French Guiana, Curaçao, Jamaica, and Aruba) in the past 24 hours. Another 6 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases (Trinidad & Tobago, Guyana, Paraguay, Belize, Bermuda, and Suriname).

- The European region reported 45.9% of daily case numbers and 41.4% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 108.04 million cases, second to the Americas in cumulative case numbers. Some countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium (16 cases), and Sweden, among others. A total of 37 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, 3 countries reporting more than 100,000, 10 reporting more than 10 000, 27 reporting over 1000 cases, and an additional 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The figures for the Eastern Mediterranean region were not updated over the last 24 hours.

- The African region reported 2.0% of daily case numbers and 1.0% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 7.54 million cases. South Africa (9858) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours followed by Botswana, Zambia, Ethiopia, Mozambique, Kenya, Zimbabwe, Uganda, Rwanda, Ghana, Cabo Verde Mauritania, and Burundi. Nigeria, Angola, Côte d'Ivoire, Mauritius, Senegal, Malawi, and Togo reported more than 500, but fewer than 1000 cases over the last 24 hours. A total of 14 countries/ territories did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 5.4% of daily case numbers and 4.9% of deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 11.84 million cases. Australia (72 357) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours followed by Viet Nam, Philippines, Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, Lao PDR, and Singapore.

- The South-East Asia region reported 5.3% of the daily newly reported cases and 4.8% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 45.40 million cases. India is dominant, reporting 117 100 cases during the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (7526). Nepal (572) and Indonesia (518) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Bangladesh, Myanmar, Sri Lanka, and the Maldives, among others, did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 6 Jan 2022, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

